CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1959, pg. 2, reads: "Constable Smith's Aides - Fifth Ward Constable Thomas J. Smith supervises the preparation of lunch for workers at the Fifth Ward's Third District polling place in Ammon Center, Tuesday. Mr. Smith is also Democratic committeeman in district, and a deputy sheriff.  Shown in the picture are C. Carter, Mrs. Adrena Allen, committeewomen, Mrs. Smith and Mrs. Rachel Carter. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: C. Carter, Adrena Allen, Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, and Rachel Carter, posed behind desk with pies in Ammon Center
